The paper is about meta-learning for few-shot learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper discusses the performance of a new method called Meta-Baseline, which is a baseline method for few-shot learning. The paper also discusses the importance of pre-training and inheriting a good few-shot classification metric. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
